Text.Value: Yet you are proof that still I will rise, and Bhaal and Myrkul will yield.
A dead Archduke is of no use to me. A living explorer - Ravengard's son, for example - is a different matter.
A dead Archduke is of no use to me. A living explorer - a githyanki of some talent, perhaps - is a different matter.
A dead Archduke is of no use to me. A living explorer - a druid of some talent, perhaps - is a different matter.
A dead Archduke is of no use to me. A living explorer - a wizard of some talent, perhaps - is a different matter.
A dead Archduke is of no use to me. A living explorer - a skilled rogue, for example - is a different matter.
A dead Archduke is of no use to me. A living explorer - a paladin of some talent - is a different matter.
A dead Archduke is of no use to me. A living explorer - a gifted bard, perhaps - is a different matter.
A dead Archduke is of no use to me. A living explorer - a mighty fighter, perhaps - is a different matter.
A dead Archduke is of no use to me. A living explorer - a sorcerer of some talent, perhaps - is a different matter.
A dead Archduke is of no use to me. A living explorer - a cleric of some talent, perhaps - is a different matter.
A dead Archduke is of no use to me. A living explorer - a mighty barbarian, for example - is a different matter.
A dead Archduke is of no use to me. A living explorer - a tadpoled fugitive with a knack for survival, perhaps - is a different matter.
She'll make herself known to you - if she hasn't already, in her own special way.
Why did you ally with Myrkul and Bhaal?
If you're not Gortash, then who are you?
And by turning mortals illithid, you deny their souls to their keepers.
One question asked. Four still remain.
Leave.
As long as mortals and immortals vie for sharper blades and louder voices, I am strengthened.
Or do not. Your lust for victory still brings you one step closer to me.
I am no agent of yours. I seek power for proper ends, not for its own sake.
Yes. Because it is the fate you've given him.
I look forward to your show of power.
*The corpse says nothing more. You did not ask a question.*
You have already laid the foundation.
You said I am proof you will rise. What did you mean?
You're much more coherent than most corpses. Why's that?
Of course you seek Orin, Bhaal's vengeful chosen. His temple is hidden even to my eyes. How fortuitous, then, that Orin seeks you.
Gortash is dead. But I am undying - just as you've made me.
Leave.
Use the Netherstones to commandeer the brain and unleash your infected army, and I will count you among my chosen.
I am Bane, the Black Lord. I am the Ultimate Tyrant. I am Fear, I am Hate.
Can you help me find the headquarters of Orin the Red?
The Steel Watch Foundry is in the Lower City near the docks. Go, and set eyes on Zariel's gift to my chosen.
*Chuckle.*
I am Bane, The Black Lord. I am the Ultimate Tyrant. I am Fear, I am Hate.
Let him suffer, then. Isn't that the fate he deserves?
It's been a century since it was submerged in Grey Harbour. You can reach it by a submersible beneath the harbour docks.
What can I do to earn your blessing, Lord Bane?
So naive for one with such cunning. Do you think it's Gortash speaking to you?
Not everyone squanders their gifts like you, Karlach.
Orin is too proud of her own handiwork to linger in your shadow. The vain don't like to be upstaged.
Ah, but you already know the answer. By making one ally, you deny them to another.
Not everyone squanders their gifts like you, Karlach.
So it is for Bhaal and Myrkul - and so it is for you. You make me eternal.
You gained my favour when you slayed Gortash. Your need for power exceeds even his.
You would ask me directions? How vexingly mundane.
How can I reach the Iron Throne?
You do not stoke fear by reaping your own fields, but by burning your foe's.
Why do red dragons ally with the githyanki? Why did the Broken God befriend Tyr?
A chance to speak to the Black Lord, and you ask him directions? How vexingly mundane.
*The corpse does not stir. It will answer no more questions.*
You seek Gortash? His soul is already suffering at my hands. That is the fate of all those who fail me.
If you're not Gortash, then who are you?
Where are the Steel Watchers assembled?
Ah, Gortash's pet project. Iron Throne Headquarters once touched the sky, a monument to martial force.
You live for power. You have proven it with every fallen foe, every chest opened, every skill claimed.
It is done. Five questions, and no more.
And you - you are the dagger that bled Myrkul's favoured. You are the thorns that prick at my sides.
